  "body": "- [v ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI want to deploy several smart-contracts (transactions) in one block.\r\nIf I do :\r\n```\r\ndeployer.deploy(Smart-contract1);\r\ndeployer.deploy(Smart-contract2);\r\n```\r\n\r\nor with await before each no result. E.g. web3.eth.getBlock(#block of transactions above) will one transaction in block (2 blocks)\r\nBut this snippet of code is work well\r\n```js\r\n...\r\nlet addressForShareLinks = async () => {\r\n   return null; // NO MATTER WHAT LOGIC THIS\r\n};\r\nmodule.exports = async function(deployer, network, addresses) {\r\n     await addressForShareLinks(); // If this line comment the result will be bad (one transactions in one block,  total 2 blocks)\r\n     await Promise.all([\r\n         deployer.deploy(Smart-contract1),\r\n         deployer.deploy(Smart-contract2)\r\n     ]);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nAnd web3.eth.getBlock(#block of transactions above) will being two transactions in one block.\r\n**NOTE!!!** In truffle this result will be bad for me. E.g. two blocks and one transaction of each. BUT in ethereum client (golang) that's what I need.\r\n\r\nWhy it's not working without await addressForShareLinks() ?\r\n\r\nI'm sorry for my english.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n- Create migrations file  with notes above.\r\n- Run migration *truffle migration --reset* \r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\nTwo transactions in one block.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\nWorking not clearly. I'm not understand. Maybe, something I do wrong.\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System:  Ubuntu 18\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache CLI v6.9.1 (ganache-core: 2.10.2) and geth 0.3.2\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v5.1.16 (core: 5.1.16)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): Node v12.14.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): ",
